<user_name>Michelle Gomes< /user_name>< text>
I love wandering around this place. There are so many interesting things to see. I spent a good amount of time looking at the cards because there were incredible - great quality with life-applicable greetings. I also found several that rendered me laughing out loud like a freak standing there in the aisle. Their children's books and gifts are creative, funny, and sweet. Paper products/gift wrap are crazy amazing. They've got great pottery and tableware, mix n match lamps and bases, unique pillows and rugs, delicious imported foods and sweets, a great display of international wines, and even furniture. This place is NOT BORING. Check it out, next time you're looking for.... anything.< /text>

I've been here many of times with my wife. This is the kind of store that you go to and you have some time and take the time to look around. We never plan to go over there to buy something in particular but it is amazing we always end up buying something. The merchandise is unique and it is fun to walk around and look at the different things from all around the world. The store even though it is filled to the brim is clean and the Isles are easily accessible.< /Review>

<Rate>5<//Rate>< review>
I like Cost Plus World Market. You can always get some unusual things here. I like a course when they have a sale cuz who doesn't like a sail! I can often find things here that I can't find at the regular supermarkets. I can find things here that she can't find out the regular types of department stores either. Sometimes they can be a little pricey, however because you're looking for some of the unusual items it's really better than having to search all over the place for those items. Although I like Amazon I do like to try to support the local businesses. So if I know they've got something here I can get it right away. It's not too much of a hassle to get there and there's plenty of parking that's free which is an important piece to me. I hate going to Downtown Sacramento celect shop the outskirts. You won't be disappointed in Cost Plus World Market as you can get some nice and usual things and then some of the usual things.</review>

<username>Charles Wassif<//username><time>1533958550016<//time><rating>1< /rating>< Text>
My experience was at Hertz was plain cold and insulting. To start, the person who was supposed to take me from the body shop to the rental agency was not pleasant, barely spoke, The only positive thing he did was help me with one of my child booster seats (they were to be transferred to the rental car, so my daughters can ride as passengers).

I was sat down and told he would be back to help me. Another associate was sitting, not taking any clients. Several customers walked in, she helped them, and I was left waiting -no acknowledgement of my wait nor were there any other reassurances. The associate who drove me to the rental agency was never to be seen after that.

I pleaded with the associate still there, she initially refused, saying the other associate would be back "he said he would be back, don't you remember?" -we're her words.

25 minutes later I pleaded with her again, she then explained the one who drove me was washing the car that I was to rent. No one asked me what car I wanted, my insurance covers the 55 dollar insurance rate, and they had chosen a car for me without my permission (the smallest car available, Nissan Versa).

I explained that I never chose a car and that I desired a car at the 55 dollar insurance rate (I pay a higher insurance premium for this). They said they had no other cars. As she said that a gentleman was returning an SUV and said it's clean and ready for me if I wanted it. Had I been asked, that would have been my request. The associate then said to wait, she checked in his car, and told me "you're getting a Dodge Journey, this car is reserved". At this point I have been waiting for over an hour, and I feel I'm being strong armed into this rental. The only reason I continued to wait was that I had familial obligations that had to be met, and I couldn't go through this process somewhere else.

The owner/manager comes in and realizes what is going on and finally begins to begin my rental agreement (for the Dodge Journey that I never chose). Due to my time constraints (after waiting there nearly two hours) they were unable to wash the car (I would have had to wait longer, and I was in desperate need to get back to my kids), and to expedite things, the owner/manager began to answer questions related to the rental agreement -some without my permission (ex. filling out the survey questionnaire with positive praise -as if it were me- I found this out when I read the rental contract).

Ultimately I was given a 36 dollar a day car when my allotment from my insurance company was and is 55 dollars a day. Toward the end of my rental I had my drop off location changed over the phone with Hertz so I would never have to see those people again. I will never go back to Hertz again and I was repeatedly mistreated and insulted by people who work at this location. This experience was absolutely unacceptable. For management to choose individuals with such poor interpersonal communication skills to work for Hertz is only a reflection of the manager/owner's poor judge of character. I will forward this to my insurance company and body shop in hopes that they use another rental agency. Avoid this place.< /Text>

<review>Edit: we have been in the rental car for almost a month, they stepped up their game when it came to the car.  they replaced the initial car with another one.  still had some staining on the rear seat, but nothing near what the first had.  the service after the first was far better, and more in tune with what we needed.  Can't say that it didn't have anything to do with my intitial impression and review here.

Jordan

Initial:

We needed a rental car because our car was in the shop.  The dealership is paying for the car at Hertz, so we were stuck with that decision.  We arrived at the location, 1 person was working at the front desk, and multiple people were heard in the background.  Upon walking into the door, the Lady at the desk asked us if we had an appointment, which my wife had made an hour prior, she yelled to the back, "Your appointment for the dealer car is here", and the lady in the back yelled back, "you take care of her."  The waiting area proceded to get busy, approximately 5 guests waiting and only 1 person up front.  Which is when 2 people from the back came up to assist.  The customer service by the people working at the desk was only problem 1.

Wife brings home the car, as I had to leave to go to work, and it is pretty filthy.  The exterior was not clean, and the interior had stains on all of the seats, and trash strewn about, in cupholders, and in the door's.  I expected more out of a car rental place, but I will guarantee that if it involves paying more, Hertz lost my family's business.

Has anyone else tried to call the 800 number to complain, or send an email using the broken link on the Hertz website?  I tried both, and got nothing.< /review>< Pics>

< Review>
Cash only. Pineapple buns are a Hong Kong food, pineapple referring to the design of the topping on the bun. So don't come expecting pineapple flavored buns. However, these buns are DELICIOUS. They have every option under the sun (bbq pork, pizza, plain, with butter) and they are all sweet, delicious and cheap. The butter buns come with A SLAB of butter. Yum!<//Review>

<user_name>Th√©r√®se Mainville</user_name>< date>
1556417063471< /date>
<rating>5< /rating><text>The first time I've tasted a pineapple bun was at this place. I've never heard of it before so I really thought it had pineapples in it. So, during my first trip, I bought one pineapple bun. When I got home, I bit into it and immediately had to tell someone how good it was!

Since I live quite far from here, I've been searching everywhere for pineapple buns and have been disappointed... The reason was because I realized pineapple bun was just a sweet bread. What I had gotten at Pineapple King Bakery was a pineapple bun with custard. I highly highly recommend it! Once I realized my mistake, I made it a quest to go there and buy as many as I can because I couldn't find it anywhere else. So this was my second trip; I bought 2 pineapple buns with custard, a pineapple bun with red bean and one with pineapple.
The one with custard is a very popular item and sells pretty quick.

So, if you don't know what a pineapple bun is, it's usually sweet bun in which the top is scored like a pineapple. The top of it looks like the skin of a pineapple.

The workers are super nice and efficient.
Since this is a small store, there are no restrooms, but there is one really close by at the Golden Gate Park in case you need one.

Overall, I would definitely keep coming back for these buns and the egg tarts :D< /text><Pics>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNDOu2UVQwZNwBifK3Yo0i6kFzCwTHHcmAD-XgZ=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNFG21OISXZBw2QP9fiOgaiuL3nkRtOP8PGuSJn=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]<//Pics><resp>None</resp>< gmap_id>

<date>1609999096824<//date><Rate>5< /Rate>< Review>
Was craving a pineapple bun with butter and saw this place offered it. I was missing Hong Kong and wasnt aware bakeries here offered the slab of butter in pineapple buns. I was super excited to try it and order some other buns as well. I ordered online and picked it up in-store. Inside is a really small bakery, but you can also pick buns inside. They put the butter in when I got there so it wouldnt melt before I got there and i was extremely impressed. The butter was huge and definitely reminded me of Hong Kong. Their plain pineapple buns are just as good. I like their spam and egg, but it does come with a lot of mayonnaise. They have other cool buns like mango pineapple buns or matcha pineapple buns. Id love to try them in the future.<//Review>

<UserId.>100420235279118081561</UserId.>< user_name>
Christopher Anderson< /user_name>
<Time>1609766336334<//Time><rating>4</rating>< review>
** During Quarantine Review **

I was casually browsing my yelp app when I saw this cute bakery just a block away. With the high ratings and limited open food options available we decided to check it out. On our visit there was a small line that formed just outside the store, but it moved very quickly.

The menu was pretty confusing and lengthy. I really had no idea what to order, but the customer in front of me said that the butter pineapple bun was the most popular and recommended the deluxe box, so we went ahead and ordered that.

My friend and I split everything and here's our verdict

I really like the pineapple bun! It has a nice sweet crusty flavor; however, my some fillings were better than others. The butter (orginal) was very lackluster to me. It tasted like the individual butter packs that you get at the diner to slather in the dinner rolls. It didn't add anything in my opinion. The matcha and custard fillings on the other-hand had that perfect amount of sweetness. The mango was way too overpowering.

Now that I know what pineapple buns taste like I think on my next visit I'll know what to order. I'd love to try the ube and I'm super curious about trying some of their savory options like spam and bbq pork. Stick to the asian flavors and you won't be disappointed!< /review>

Hidden gem in the area they have amazing pineapple cream buns I particularly enjoyed the matcha cream. It's only $1.60 for two buns super great value! They have different breads as well from sweet to savory!  The pork buns are worth checking out as well!

They only take cash so make sure you have some before you get there.

They also do phone orders if you're ordering large orders for parties. Service is pretty quick if it's an empty shop but if there's a line prepared to wait about 5-10 minutes extra, but overall it's a pretty quick in and out trip.

There's no tables here to enjoy your treats unfortunately. There is also no bathroom here either .< /Text>

< Text>
Decided to come by here because the flavored pineapple buns I saw were really interesting. They have other buns that is really cheap and worth getting like your average Chinese bakery. They even have a combo meal where you can get certain buns and a drink for around $4ish. My husband got the combo meal B which has Milk Tea, spam & egg bun, and mini pineapple bun. We didn't really enjoy the milk tea as much maybe we were use to a more smoother taste from NY. The spam and egg bun was really good. I ordered the Pineapple matcha bun and the pineapple lychee bun. I really enjoy both the buns. I can taste the flavors if you keep eating and really sit and try to taste the fillings, but I wish both the matcha and the lychee had a little bit more flavor. Overall, it was pretty decent and definitely a cheap eats place.</Text>

<name>Emily Yush Yuen<//name><rating>5</rating>< Time>
1621654565521< /Time>
< Text>
As a Hong Kong local, I maintain that this Hong Kong style bakery bakes bread that beats most Hong Kong bakeries. They reheat bread on request. Their pineapple bun is indeed the best, with a crispy topping atop a soft bun. All their breads are however, superb. Their pastries are also excellent - the taro pastry has just the right amount of sweetness to bring out the taro flavour. And to top this all off is their Hong Kong milk tea, especially when made by Ivy, beats ALL Hong Kong milk tea places. The tea is stronger than expresso coffee, smooth and is perfectly sweet at regular sweetness. I'd go every day if cholesterol wasn't a concern.</Text>

My little cousin had her 15 here. The venue gets the job done. It's not ugly. What ruins this place is the security. When your guest are entering they make you stop and look inside your car to see how many people are in the car. I've never been to a venue who does that. After the last song they were forcing us out. There were still people there and they were just throwing them out. Mind you we had a ton of stuff to load up and they are trying to rush us. I would never book this place. Finally when everything was loaded we had to drive outside the gate to figure out where my uncle wanted the stuff to go. They just shut the gate.< /Review>

<date>1622125718546< /date><gmap_id>0x80dc749f6002c2b3:0xe3458b1592fae094<//gmap_id>< text>
I rarely post reviews for products online as I'm seldom impressed with a product enough to do so.  However, in this instance I feel compelled to shout this one from the rooftops!  I am the full time caregiver for my 64 spouse who I've been married to for 46 years.  She has Type II diabetes among other serious maladies, but her blood sugar drops dangerously low without warning, often in her sleep.  With the new Libre II device monitoring her levels in real time and sounding the alarm, we are able to promptly react before she goes into hypoglycemic shock.  Just as amazing is the predictive nature of the device that forecasts rising or falling trends of her lab values thus allowing us to adjust diet and other factors resulting using less insulin.  It is a game changer for us!  Finally, we are so grateful to Advanced Diabetes Supply for guiding us through the process of obtaining the device, coordinating medical records, insurance company requirements and keeping us posted every step of the way!  We dealt with a person by the name of Izzy who was professional, compassionate and kind. Thank you from the bottom of our hearts.  Please feel free to use any or all of this review.  Terry & Carrie Herman, Preston, CT</text>

<review>**FINAL UPDATE**
At first, I was very unhappy with ADS customer service for the reasons below. However, ADS was extremely proactive in remedying the situation and now I am extremely satisfied. As soon as my insurance approved the authorization, ADS got my order ready and out the door. I believe that my initial experience was not representative of ADS as a whole and I applaud their customer service department for going above and beyond to make sure I could get my supplies as fast as possible.

**UPDATE**
So, I'm actually really impressed with ADS customer service! Less than one day after I posted the original review, a rep contacted me and helped me get everything sorted out. It turns out we do need some more paperwork (which I found a little frustrating, because I was told multiple times by multiple reps that they had all the paperwork necessary and all I had to do was wait), but hopefully that was the last of the miscommunication. They also apologized for the lack of communication on behalf of the company and even offered to overnight me some testing materials so that I can check my blood sugars in the meantime. This interaction makes me hopeful that my previous experience with ADS was not representative of their customer service. I don't like leaving bad reviews on yelp, but I think that a company that deals with life-saving medical supplies should be held to a higher standard than say, a coffee shop. I will update this review hopefully just one more time after everything works out and I actually get my G6 system!

I've been trying to get on the Dexcom G6 and my experience with Advanced Diabetes Supply has extremely been frustrating. The process of getting the supplies I need has been delayed multiple times because different reps keep giving me the wrong information. They even sent a text message that an authorization had been submitted, but when I called to check in, it actually had not been submitted. To their credit, every rep I spoke to has been very friendly. My experience is detailed below:

ADS: "We spoke with your doctor's office yesterday, we have all the paperwork, and everything looks good. We'll give you a call when things are ready."

Me: *calls to check in two weeks later*

ADS: "Actually, we need your doctor's office to send us a form so we can send it to your insurance. After we get that, it'll take about a week for your insurance to approve it."

Me: ??? then why did you tell me everything was good and have me wait two weeks for nothing??? *Has doctor submit necessary paperwork in less than one day. calls ADS to check in a week later."

ADS: "Yes, we have all the paperwork and we just have to submit an authorization to your insurance. I'll submit it now, check back in a few days."

**They actually sent me a text message which states that the authorization was submitted as urgent and everything should be approved in about a week.

Me: *calls back a few days later to check AGAIN*

ADS: "Your authorization hasn't been submitted.... Yes, I see that someone sent you that text message, but they didn't actually submit the authorization. I'll submit it now and everything should be ready in about a week."

Me: ??????? Your company literally sent me a text message that my authorization had been submitted as "URGENT" and that I would only have to wait another week. Now my process of waiting a week is starting over??

Extremely frustrating... will be calling back tomorrow to see if they actually submitted the authorization.<//review>< Pics>

<text>Stopped here after spotting it while driving by. Really glad that we did. We ordered the Philly Cheesesteaks and I got a mocha frappuccino. The sandwiches were huge! The bread was fresh and toasted just right so it was crunchy on the outside but still hot and soft on the inside. The ratio of meat to bun to cheese was perfect. The vegetables were also cooked to perfection and the cheese was fully melted. The frappuccino was delicious as well, not too much chocolate like a lot of places tend to do. < Text>
Always a great little uphill hike with a spectacular view! Dog friendly, people friendly and not too long at right around 4 miles round trip. Views in all directions but the views north over Shasta Lake dam to Mt Shasta and west looking down on the Sacramento River and out toward whiskey town are beautiful.  My Shasta was clothed in clouds this day.<//Text>

Beautiful views, easily one of the best hikes in the area! I have been at various times in the year, always well maintained and worthwhile.

I asked them for old furnace checkup. It had an issue and we ended up a new furnace. They did it in a half day: 5, I met and spoke with 4-5 employees. My problem was no cold air when A/C was on. I called another service company first who misdiagnosed the problem. They then discovered I had a refrigerant leak in the system somewhere but unable to test for the leak.  I called SC and they responded with a sense of urgency. <review>Chronology of events (latest to earliest)
Encounter 3: Jan 2021: 2nd Furnace purchased (1st purchase as noted below, 2 AC Compressors + 1 Furnace)

4.5 **** for their service techs (mostly excellent, knowledgeable, helpful, and goes the extra mile, with very few exceptions) Khaled continues to excel whenever he comes to service the equipment
3.5 *** for their installation techs. This time, they failed to ground the furnace and disconnect box - basic items that "should" to be done right the first time?! As a result, the "impossible to get hold of SJ City Inspection" failed, and more hassles to get the equipment certified.
3.0*** for the Customer Service - very friendly people, but not knowledgeable and has absolutely no power over their tyrannical Tech Dept. They will give many platitudes to placate the customer, but advise is to immediately request to talk to Tech Dept, otherwise one would have to repeat multiple times the same inputs since the Tech Dept almost never calls back after CS promises they will.
1.5** for Tech Dept. Does not call back until multiple escalation is made. Comes across as arrogant, not particularly helpful. They will fix the problem they created but only after one manages to get to them. (Monica seems to be the only responsive one in that department, Tye has not called back or responded at all both the times I had issues)
0.5* Sales. They will promise you the world, but disappears after the sale. In both my purchases, my Salesman promised a smooth process (ie installation and paperwork specifics - I was clear with my concerns then, and for this latest purchase, especially with the city certification, knowing the grief SJ City will cause). In the first case, they put it down to a "miscommunication" but they finally helped (after escalation) with the City Inspection.  Despite committing to "take care of inspection process and make it transparent to me", during the sales process, now I have a problem with City inspection, and they are nowhere to be found. I have called them but no call back, no sign of anything.

Now, I might expect Alicia or their CS manager to respond to this - seems like the response happens only the customer is extremely annoyed.

So should you go with them? IMHO for general maintenance, if you are not too particular about pricing, a convenient approach.
For new systems, imho "caveat emptor". Some days, you can be made to feel you are the center of their service. Other days just feel like it is too much work to be worth it. (like now)

But as a reminder to myself - I won't be silly to look here for my third upgrade! I really have to stop being so trusting!

Encounter 2: Oct 2019 >>Installation of 2 New ACs/1 Furnace + remedial work on missed installation items-failed City Inspection + subsequent maintenance work
** Update after multiple interactions... Not quite 5 Stars.. service and competency level varied across techs. Some problems encountered: installation of ac compressors not to city code. Minor rework needed. Missed a scheduled appointment totally. New ac compressor not cooling after 6 months. (imagine an approx $10k equipment not working after 6months!) LeamkimgLeaking coolant that couldn't be traced. No dye available to inject to trace leakage, have to return to redo. Problems to be expected but it just means tying up my time waiting for appointments, which I have to follow up on (did not call back to reschedule as promised) To be fair reasonably responsive, although their CS not very capable beyond the superficial greetings and perhaps scheduling work (even then).

Encounter 1: Fall 2019 :Service maintenance on old AC/Heaters
Khaled was the tech that helped me out today. Very timely, detailed in checking out all the issues and helpful with suggestions. Made very good observations and was very polite and kind.

This company seems to have done a good job training their staff and they seem to know what they are doing. Good job!</review>< Pictures>

<text>Chronology of events (latest to earliest)
Encounter 3: Jan 2021: 2nd Furnace purchased (1st purchase as noted below, 2 AC Compressors + 1 Furnace)

4.5 **** for their service techs (mostly excellent, knowledgeable, helpful, and goes the extra mile, with very few exceptions) Khaled continues to excel whenever he comes to service the equipment
3.5 *** for their installation techs. This time, they failed to ground the furnace and disconnect box - basic items that "should" to be done right the first time?! As a result, the "impossible to get hold of SJ City Inspection" failed, and more hassles to get the equipment certified.
3.0*** for the Customer Service - very friendly people, but not knowledgeable and has absolutely no power over their tyrannical Tech Dept. They will give many platitudes to placate the customer, but advise is to immediately request to talk to Tech Dept, otherwise one would have to repeat multiple times the same inputs since the Tech Dept almost never calls back after CS promises they will.
1.5** for Tech Dept. Does not call back until multiple escalation is made. Comes across as arrogant, not particularly helpful. They will fix the problem they created but only after one manages to get to them. (Monica seems to be the only responsive one in that department, Tye has not called back or responded at all both the times I had issues)
0.5* Sales. They will promise you the world, but disappears after the sale. In both my purchases, my Salesman promised a smooth process (ie installation and paperwork specifics - I was clear with my concerns then, and for this latest purchase, especially with the city certification, knowing the grief SJ City will cause). In the first case, they put it down to a "miscommunication" but they finally helped (after escalation) with the City Inspection.  Despite committing to "take care of inspection process and make it transparent to me", during the sales process, now I have a problem with City inspection, and they are nowhere to be found. I have called them but no call back, no sign of anything.

Now, I might expect Alicia or their CS manager to respond to this - seems like the response happens only the customer is extremely annoyed.

So should you go with them? IMHO for general maintenance, if you are not too particular about pricing, a convenient approach.
For new systems, imho "caveat emptor". Some days, you can be made to feel you are the center of their service. Other days just feel like it is too much work to be worth it. (like now)

But as a reminder to myself - I won't be silly to look here for my third upgrade! I really have to stop being so trusting!

Encounter 2: Oct 2019 >>Installation of 2 New ACs/1 Furnace + remedial work on missed installation items-failed City Inspection + subsequent maintenance work
** Update after multiple interactions... Not quite 5 Stars.. service and competency level varied across techs. Some problems encountered: installation of ac compressors not to city code. Minor rework needed. Missed a scheduled appointment totally. New ac compressor not cooling after 6 months. (imagine an approx $10k equipment not working after 6months!) LeamkimgLeaking coolant that couldn't be traced. No dye available to inject to trace leakage, have to return to redo. Problems to be expected but it just means tying up my time waiting for appointments, which I have to follow up on (did not call back to reschedule as promised) To be fair reasonably responsive, although their CS not very capable beyond the superficial greetings and perhaps scheduling work (even then).

Encounter 1: Fall 2019 :Service maintenance on old AC/Heaters
Khaled was the tech that helped me out today. Very timely, detailed in checking out all the issues and helpful with suggestions. Made very good observations and was very polite and kind.

This company seems to have done a good job training their staff and they seem to know what they are doing. Good job!</text>< pics>

On 8/25/17 Ben Carter came to figure out a recurring drainage problem. Water was consistently flowing from the pan overflow pipe above and just outside our front door instead of the primary pipe into the ground a few feet away. Thinking out of the box, Ben determined that air was forcing the water in the wrong direction, and that he needed to replumb the pvc drainage system in the attic. <rate>3</rate><Review>Thinking of the overall experience of evaluating the HVAC system, I'm only neutral because the system is working well for our needs, but each time a technician comes to check it out, much of the time is spent trying to show that the system should be replaced.  Very little time is spent improving or repairing.  As an example:  there is always some rust in areas where condensate collects.  No time has ever been used cleaning it off and maybe spraying the area with a rust converter (which there are many of now).  The extractor fan impellor is easily miss-aligned and occasionally rubs on the housing.  Someone could have replaced the soft mounting parts.  Instead I quite often have to re-align the unit after the tech leaves and the furnace starts for the first time.
Nick is obviously a very well trained technician, and it was a good experience talking with him and seeing him check out both the condensing system and the furnace.  However, the focus has always been on evaluating for purposes of replacement.  I'd like to see more emphasis on maintenance and repair with the goal of extending the life of my investment.  So far I feel like I've paid a lot for diagnostics and evaluation.
Your prices for replacement of the system are not competitive.
This "maintenance program" doesn't seem to be working for me.

That was from prior visits.
Lee's visit was somewhat  better.  He listened and responded to my interests in the system.  However I still had to adjust the small fan as before. Very little time is spent improving or repairing.  As an example:  there is always some rust in areas where condensate collects.  No time has ever been used cleaning it off and maybe spraying the area with a rust converter (which there are many of now).  The extractor fan impellor is easily miss-aligned and occasionally rubs on the housing.  Someone could have replaced the soft mounting parts.  Instead I quite often have to re-align the unit after the tech leaves and the furnace starts for the first time.
Nick is obviously a very well trained technician, and it was a good experience talking with him and seeing him check out both the condensing system and the furnace.  However, the focus has always been on evaluating for purposes of replacement.  I'd like to see more emphasis on maintenance and repair with the goal of extending the life of my investment.  So far I feel like I've paid a lot for diagnostics and evaluation.
Your prices for replacement of the system are not competitive.
This "maintenance program" doesn't seem to be working for me.

That was from prior visits.
Lee's visit was somewhat  better.  He listened and responded to my interests in the system.  However I still had to adjust the small fan as before.  An after closure heat check would have saved me having to open it up and adjusting it to get it to run.  Lee has excellent knowledge of the system.< /text><Pictures>None< /Pictures>< resp>

< Text>
When our Amana furnace heat exchanger was diagnosed with hairline cracks by our regular service company, we asked Service Champions to give us a second opinion.

On 10/10, Tyler Shook inspected our heater and did not find a failure but showed me that it was worn and stressed after 17 years of use. I asked to speak with a salesman, so he called his office and Chris Lucas arrived a few minutes later. Both Chris and Tyler spent 2 hours helping me choose a new heat pump/furnace system that fit well with our existing solar panel installation. I was very pleased with the knowledge and care that Tyler and Chris showed in helping me find the best/efficient  system to fit our budget.

Tyler, Chris, and Washington all did very well for me and Service Champions.

<review>Had my furnace replaced by Service Champions on 9/27/2016.
First I want to get on the record  that the two installers were curteous, professional, respectful and knowledgable.
The SC moto is if you are not happy its free! Im not looking for anything free but do want to share my total expertience. I told both men that I was extremely picky and expected the quality of the removal and installation to be perfect; quality of workmanship, cleanliness, protection of surrounding infrastructure, door jams interion of heater closet and enrty / exit doorway etc.
There were three issues with the installation that I was not happy with.
1. The door jams and interior cabinet drywall were damaged with the removal and installation . These areas should have been protected with tape or barriers before the work started.
2. The heater closet door was left with greese handprints inside an outside as was the door used to enter and exit the work area.
3. The new thermostat was not mounted  flush with the wall. The plastic molly dry wall inserts were sticking out about 1/8 inch and therefore the thermostat wall plate did not sit flush against the wall. I had to remove the thermostat to fill the old mounting holes and to paint the area because the new thermostat is smaller than the old thermostat. I had to replace the plastic molly inserts and reinstall the thermostat.
I did not catch thes issues until i got home at the end of the day. I was not at home for the whole installation process.
It is clear that these service representatives are well trained and capable technically but I expected a higher level of overall attention to detail. That level of attention is most likely not taught in the training they receive and in my opinion has to be part of the basic makeup of the individual, part of his personal performance DNA if you will.
Overall I was comfortable with the work done and would have Service Champions back in my house. I am a gold member, SC does the yearly system inspections and services my HVAC units.  They are not the least expensive HVAC contractor out there by far so my performance expectations are higher when the price is higher.</review></record></dataset><record>

<name>Joel Grossman</name><Date>1360794815397< /Date>< Rate>
2< /Rate>
< text>
I have a Trane XE70 gas furnance and it hasn't been working properly. I called Service Champions due to their history in the area and an add in the mail to come out, complete a tune up, and diagnose the problem. This was back in 2010 and the technician did the "tune up" and stated I needed a new furnance that would run me around $15k. He stated however if I just mess with a couple of wires the heater would ignite. I didn't bother doing anything with it since I was able to pull on some wires (recommended by a Service Champion employee which is a liability in itself) however this latest season has been pretty cold and pulling on the wires has not been working very well. I did 10-15 minutes research online and discovered I just need to replace the gas valve part #VAL09377 as per a diagnosis from a Trane technician who knew of this common problem with this model furnance. I called Service Champions and advised of the last visit in 2010 that was very unhelpful and seemed as prior reviews a scam and was blown off told that it was back in 2010 and they are under different management (same company). I was told they would take a whole $30 off of another visit (I live 2 miles away from their store) and it would only cost $40 to come back out. I told them I might call them back. I am in the customer service industry and this is by far not the way to take care of a situation like this. When a customer calls again even after feeling taken advantage of, try to give you another chance for a sale, and they express a concern why would you not try to make it right or direct the customer's concern to someone that can? I would not recommend this company to ANYONE. Do your own research online to diagnose the problem and then call around for an estimate for the labor only. Buy the part yourself.</text>
